l\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vdf1665702921432.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vdf1665702921432.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vdf1665702921432.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vdf1665702921432\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Analyzing Access Paths\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__analyzing_access_paths_140212\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Access path analysis plays an important role in performance optimization, because access paths affect database I/O processing. Analyzing access paths is part of the process of designing an optimal data model.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__p_d45668e1_d45669e1_d45670e1\">A business activity gains access to its user view by activating components. A component can access the entities directly or it can access them indirectly by invoking other components. Access path analysis is a technique to establish the impact of a component on the system load by directly accessing the entities that represent the data.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__p_d45671e1_d45672e1_d45673e1\">The purpose of access path analysis is to:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__li_d22790e1_d22791e1_d22792e1\">Verify whether the modeled entities support the user views\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__li_d22793e1_d22794e1_d22795e1\">Identify potential processing bottlenecks caused by accessing the application's database\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__p_d45674e1_d45675e1_d45676e1\">Access path analysis can be performed at different stages of the system life cycle. It is particularly useful during the design stage when the major decisions are taken that determine whether an application model sufficiently supports a certain user view and whether performance bottlenecks are to be expected.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__topic_d29667e1_d29668e1_d29669e1_d29670e1_d29671e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__p_d45680e1_d45681e1_d45682e1\">To perform access path analysis, follow these steps for the components you decide to prototype:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__li_d22796e1_d22797e1_d22798e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__p_d45683e1_d45684e1_d45685e1\">Choose the user views to analyze, based on the\n                  core business requirements and associated risks. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mut1665702921504.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mut1665702921504.html\" title=\"A user view comprises the data needed for a business activity. The data can come from more than one modeled entity. Do not confuse the user view with the user interface of the application.\">Identify and Prioritize User Views</a>. </p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__li_d22799e1_d22800e1_d22801e1\">Implement the data design for the selected user views by defining modeled entities, fields, keys, and relationships.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__li_d22802e1_d22803e1_d22804e1\">Define frames-within-frames component designs to establish the access paths. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ntc1665702921573.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ntc1665702921573.html\" title=\"Components give access to the user view of a business activity. A crucial part of the design of a Uniface component is the frames-within-frames diagram. Access path analysis requires a frames-within-frames definition for the Uniface component under consideration.\">Frames-Within-Frames Design</a>.\n                  </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__li_d22805e1_d22806e1_d22807e1\">Analyze the access paths based on estimated data\n               volumes to identify those that have the highest access stress rates. You can use the\n               resulting access profile and statistics to adjust your data design before testing, or\n               to identify the components to prototype and test first. <p class=\"p\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__p_d45686e1_d45687e1_d45688e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sjw1665702921651.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sjw1665702921651.html\" title=\"The modeled objects and the component data structure provide basic information about the component entities and access paths. This is information that you need to make correct estimates of the volumes and changing rates of the data in the information system.\">Component Entities and Paths</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rdv1665702921790.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rdv1665702921790.html\" title=\"The access profile is the sequence of all access paths needed by a user view.\">Access Profiles and Statistics</a>. </p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__li_d22808e1_d22809e1_d22810e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__p_d45689e1_d45690e1_d45691e1\">Create prototype components and test the data design with respect to benchmarking and providing contingencies for the risks.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__li_d22811e1_d22812e1_d22813e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vdf1665702921432__p_d45692e1_d45693e1_d45694e1\">Refine the modeled objects. For more\n                  information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"okg1665702921881.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/okg1665702921881.html\" title=\"After completing the access path analysis, you can choose to refine the modeled entities, fields, keys, and relationships.\">Refining the Modeled Objects</a>. </p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532970\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532970\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Analyzing Access Paths Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Analyzing Access Paths Access path analysis plays an important role in performance optimization, because access paths affect database I/O processing. Analyzing access paths is part of the process of designing an optimal data model. A business activity gains access to its user view by activating components. A component can access the entities directly or it can access them indirectly by invoking other components. Access path analysis is a technique to establish the impact of a component on the system load by directly accessing the entities that represent the data. The purpose of access path analysis is to: Verify whether the modeled entities support the user views Identify potential processing bottlenecks caused by accessing the application's database Access path analysis can be performed at different stages of the system life cycle. It is particularly useful during the design stage when the major decisions are taken that determine whether an application model sufficiently supports a certain user view and whether performance bottlenecks are to be expected. To perform access path analysis, follow these steps for the components you decide to prototype: Choose the user views to analyze, based on the core business requirements and associated risks. For more information, see Identify and Prioritize User Views . Implement the data design for the selected user views by defining modeled entities, fields, keys, and relationships. Define frames-within-frames component designs to establish the access paths. For more information, see Frames-Within-Frames Design . Analyze the access paths based on estimated data volumes to identify those that have the highest access stress rates. You can use the resulting access profile and statistics to adjust your data design before testing, or to identify the components to prototype and test first. For more information, see Component Entities and Paths and Access Profiles and Statistics . Create prototype components and test the data design with respect to benchmarking and providing contingencies for the risks. Refine the modeled objects. For more information, see Refining the Modeled Objects . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}